==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oxamic
<hw>Ox*am"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ox</ets>alic +
<ets>am</ets>ido]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or
designating, an acid <chform>NH2.CO.CO.HO</chform> obtained as a fine
crystalline powder, intermediate between oxalic acid and oxamide. Its
ammonium salt is obtained by boiling oxamide with ammonia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oxamide</ent>⟦br⟧
